description.displayText: When looking for child care, my husband and I had a lot of apprehension in trusting someone else with the care of our 7 month old daughter. Upon interviewing Liz, she put our apprehensions at ease immediately. Her certifications and experience made her stand out among the rest. She has a realist attitude, which we love. The care she provides our daughter is wonderful and we are so thankful to have found her. She is punctual, communicative, inventive, and always shows up with a smile on her face (even at 5 a.m.). We truly don't know what we would have done had we not found her.

Elizabeth was wonderful with my daughter.    I was in Atlanta for work and contacted Elizabeth a few days before , she was very prompt & professional.
She sent photos through out the day and definitely put my mind to ease.   She was awesome and I wish she wasn't so far away I'd hire her full time!

description.displayText: Immediate hire. I contacted Liz the day of due to some family changes and not only was she able to accommodate, but she kept me updated with was going on in the day with my son. She aided in his potty training schedule, took him to the pool, the museum, and more. I felt more than comfortable with her childcare skills that I sent him with her an additional day. Glad she was available and will be looking to make her a PT nanny in the future as our schedule dictates. Definitely recommend. 5 out of 5 stars! Thanks again Liz!

description.displayText: I would highly recommend Liz because she takes a holistic approach to childcare, offering assistance in not only caring for my son but gave me input on family planning, his schedule, baby products, and eating/sleeping habits. Me and my wife are grateful for her help and if my wife goes back to work, she will be the first person we call. Thanks Liz!

description.displayText: At first, I was worried about leaving my daughter with a sitter but Liz eased my fears right away. She is simply the best! She is a true professional, knowing exactly what we were thinking and would text us before I had a chance to text her. Since that first encounter, she has become a regular watching my 8 year old daughter. I highly recommend her.

description.displayText: Elizabeth is a great babysitter. I chose her on care.com due to her profile, the (14) five star ratings, and the comments from all of the families. The families were right, Elizabeth is truly Five Stars. My son loves her playful energy and we as parents love her educational approach when interacting with our child. She promotes good manners and respectful behavior and displays the same herself. She stuck to my sons schedule and communicated with me throughout the evening while I was out. She's the perfect package: a babysitter, a teacher, a nurse, and a friend.

description.displayText: Liz was our nanny for 5 months and was a total lifesaver for our family and became part of our family. We would have kept her for a long time, but moved from NYC to CA. My son was 3 months when Liz started and she helped me navigate the tricky waters of being a first time nervous mom :) She helped get my son on a schedule and when he started waking up in the night, adjusted his daytime schedule without me asking to help ensure longer sleep overnight. She logged his feedings and diapers and kept me up to date throughout the day with texts and photos when I went back to work.  She is very outgoing and keeps busy - she took my son to a class every day, rain or shine! One of the owners of a nearby baby class even commented to me about how great she was with my son.  She has great instincts with infants, and had a hat on my son starting in October - the only time he got sick the entire time she worked with us was over the holidays when she wasn't there! Her next family is lucky to have her!
